  <div>
      <h2>Admissions, academic and career advising</h2><p dir="ltr" id="docs-internal-guid-52b8c69d-7fff-510c-a951-c979eea197a2">iSchool staff are here to help provide you with quality support throughout your iSchool experience as you explore, develop and pursue opportunities that align with your life and career goals. Advising hours and scheduling instructions are listed below for graduate admissions, academic and career advisors. Most programs host appointments online or in-person.</p><h3>Consult an academic advisor for topics such as:</h3><ul><li dir="ltr">Academic guidance such as degree planning, course registration and suggestions, Capstone and internships.</li><li dir="ltr">Policies, procedures and forms at the UW, Graduate School, iSchool or degree program level</li><li dir="ltr">Approval of transfer credits, out-of-school courses, etc.</li><li dir="ltr">Navigating other UW offices/services (i.e., Financial Aid, International Programs, etc.)</li></ul><h3>Consult a career advisor for topics such as:</h3><ul><li dir="ltr">Internship and career opportunities, employer contact info and advice</li><li dir="ltr">Resume and cover letter reviews</li><li dir="ltr">Preparing for job interviews: mock interviews, day-of interview tips, salary negotiation, etc.</li></ul><hr><h2>Contact an advisor</h2><ul><li dir="ltr"><a href="#info">Bachelor of Science in Informatics</a></li><li dir="ltr"><a href="#grad">Graduate admission advising</a></li><li dir="ltr"><a href="#muse">Master of Arts in Museology</a></li><li dir="ltr"><a href="#mlis">Master of Library and Information Science (MLIS)</a></li><li dir="ltr"><a href="#law">Master of Library and Information Science - Law Librarianship (MLIS Law)</a></li><li dir="ltr"><a href="#msim">Master of Science in Information Management (MSIM)</a></li><li dir="ltr"><a href="#phd">Ph.D. in Information Science</a></li><li dir="ltr"><a href="#career">Career advisors</a></li><li dir="ltr"><a href="https://ischool.uw.edu/advising-support/peer-advisors">Informatics Peer Advisors</a></li></ul><p><a name="info"></a></p><h3>Bachelor of Science in Informatics</h3><ul><li><strong>Email</strong>: <a href="mailto:informatics@uw.edu" target="_blank">informatics@uw.edu</a></li><li><strong>Current Informatics Majors</strong><ul><li>Quick Questions Drop-Ins<ul><li>Use the <a class="inline_disabled external" href="https://forms.office.com/r/rjEeNzXSkS" target="_blank">Quick Questions Check-In form</a> to join the queue when you're ready to chat. A peer or academic advisor will help you when it's your turn.</li><li>Winter Quarter (1/5/26-3/13/26)<ul><li>Drop-ins available Mon-Thurs 11am-2pm - email <a href="mailto:informatics@uw.edu" target="_blank">informatics@uw.edu</a> for questions</li></ul></li><li>Temporary cancellations and changes to advising hours will be posted on the check-in form. Quick Questions is not held on holidays or breaks between quarters.</li></ul></li><li>Schedule a&nbsp;<a class="external" href="https://tinyurl.com/INFOAdvisorVirtual" target="_blank">Zoom-based</a> or&nbsp;<a class="external" href="https://tinyurl.com/INFOAdvisorInPerson" target="_blank">in-person</a> appointment<strong> </strong>with an academic advisor. Who is my assigned advisor?<ul><li>Dowell Eugenio for last names A-G</li><li>Christina Murray for last names H-N</li><li>Kathy Mitchell for last names O-Z</li><li>To provide the best possible support, we reserve scheduled appointments for discussions that are more complex or require additional time. This includes topics such as concerns about academic progress or personal matters that may be impacting your education.</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><strong>Informatics Minors</strong><ul><li>Email: <a href="mailto:INFOMinors@uw.edu">INFOMinors@uw.edu</a></li><li>Advising: Talk to a peer or academic advisor during Quick Question Drop-Ins. Use the <a class="inline_disabled external" href="https://forms.office.com/r/rjEeNzXSkS" target="_blank">Quick Questions Check-In form</a> to join the queue when you're ready to chat.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Prospective Informatics Students</strong><ul><li>Email: <a href="mailto:iask@uw.edu">iask@uw.edu</a></li><li>Information Sessions: Attend an online&nbsp;<a href="https://ischool.uw.edu/events">Informatics Program Overview presentation</a>&nbsp;to learn more about the Informatics program.</li><li>Quick Question Drop-Ins: Talk to a peer or academic advisor during Quick Question Drop-Ins. Use the <a class="inline_disabled external" href="https://forms.office.com/r/rjEeNzXSkS" target="_blank">Quick Questions Check-In form</a> to join the queue when you're ready to chat.</li><li>Prospective students can <a href="https://outlook.office.com/book/InformaticsStudentServicesProspectiveStudentAdvising@cloud.washington.edu/?ismsaljsauthenabled">schedule an advising appointment here</a>. Online and in-person options available.</li></ul></li></ul><p><a name="grad"></a></p><h3>Graduate admissions advising</h3><p>Meet with the graduate admissions advisor to have your questions answered 1-on-1 about the MSIM, MLIS or Ph.D. in Information Science programs.&nbsp;</p><ul><li dir="ltr"><p><a href="https://calendly.com/emorbuc-uw">Schedule a 30-minute meeting</a><br>Zoom or in person</p><p>For additional questions regarding admissions, contact <a href="mailto:iask@uw.edu">iask@uw.edu.</a></p></li></ul><p><a name="muse"></a></p><h3>Master of Arts in Museology</h3><ul><li><strong>Kevin Glatt</strong>, Museology graduate advisor<ul><li>Contact: <a href="mailto:uwmuse@uw.edu">uwmuse@uw.edu</a></li><li>Current and prospective students can <a href="https://calendly.com/kglatt/prospective-student-meetings?month=2024-01">schedule an advising appointment.</a></li><li>Advising appointments are available online.</li></ul></li></ul><p><a name="mlis"></a></p><h3>Master of Library and Information Science (MLIS)</h3><ul><li><strong>Jennifer Siembor, </strong>MLIS academic advisor<ul><li>Contact for current students:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:mlis@uw.edu">mlis@uw.edu</a></li><li>Current&nbsp;MLIS students can&nbsp;<a href="https://outlook.office365.com/book/iSchoolStudentServices1@cloud.washington.edu/">schedule an advising appointment</a></li></ul></li><li>Current students can connect with the MLIS peer advisors, email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:mlisadvising@uw.edu">mlisadvising@uw.edu</a>. (MLIS peer advisors will not be available over the summer.)</li><li>If you are a prospective student, please reach out to <a href="mailto:iask@uw.edu">iask@uw.edu</a> for questions about the admissions process or applications or <a href="https://calendly.com/emorbuc-uw">schedule a 30-minute meeting</a> with the admissions advisor.&nbsp;</li></ul><p><a name="law"></a></p><h3>Master of Library and Information Science - Law Librarianship (MLIS Law)</h3><ul><li><strong>Jennifer Siembor, </strong>academic advisor<ul><li>Contact for registration questions<ul><li>Current students can contact:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:mlis@uw.edu">mlis@uw.edu</a></li><li>Current&nbsp;MLIS Law students can&nbsp;<a href="https://outlook.office365.com/book/iSchoolStudentServices1@cloud.washington.edu/">schedule an advising appointment</a></li></ul></li></ul></li><li><strong>Carla Wale,&nbsp;</strong>Director of MLIS Law Librarianship program<ul><li>Contact for academic or career advising: <a href="mailto:cpwale@uw.edu">cpwale@uw.edu</a>&nbsp;</li></ul></li><li>If you are a prospective student, please reach out to <a href="mailto:iask@uw.edu">iask@uw.edu</a> for questions about the admissions process or applications or <a href="https://calendly.com/emorbuc-uw">schedule a 30-minute meeting</a> with the admissions advisor.</li></ul><p><a name="msim"></a></p><h3>Master of Science in Information Management (MSIM)</h3><ul><li><strong>Email: </strong><a href="mailto:msim@uw.edu">msim@uw.edu</a></li><li><strong>Current Students: </strong><a href="https://outlook.office365.com/owa/calendar/iSchoolStudentServicesMSIM@cloud.washington.edu/bookings/">Schedule an appointment</a>, options for online and in person appointments available.</li><li><strong>Advising Team</strong><ul><li><strong>Iris Cao, </strong>MSIM Early-Career and Mid-Career academic advisor</li><li><strong>Cameron Cramer, </strong>MSIM Early-Career &amp; Early-Career Accelerated academic advisor</li></ul></li><li><strong>Peer Advisors:</strong> To connect with the MSIM peer advisors:<ul><li>Contact:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:msimpeeradvisors@uw.edu">msimpeeradvisors@uw.edu</a>.</li><li>Schedule a <a href="https://outlook.office365.com/book/MSIMPeerFacilitators@cloud.washington.edu/">MSIM peer advisors appointment here</a>.</li></ul></li></ul><p><a name="phd"></a></p><h3>Ph.D. in Information Science</h3><ul><li><strong>Andrea Gnessin,</strong> Ph.D. Academic Advisor<ul><li>Contact for current students:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:ischoolphd@uw.edu">ischoolphd@uw.edu</a></li><li>Current Ph.D. students can<a href="https://outlook.office365.com/owa/calendar/PhDStudentServices@cloud.washington.edu/bookings/"> schedule advising appointments</a></li><li>Advising appointments are available online or in person for current students.</li></ul></li><li>If you are a prospective student, please reach out to <a href="mailto:iask@uw.edu">iask@uw.edu</a> for questions about the admissions process or applications or <a href="https://calendly.com/emorbuc-uw">schedule a 30-minute meeting</a> with the admissions advisor.</li></ul><p><a name="career"></a></p><h3>Career advisors</h3><ul><li>Contact:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:icareers@uw.edu">icareers@uw.edu</a></li><li>For current iSchool students, <a href="https://uw.joinhandshake.com/stu/appointments/new">schedule an appointment via Handshake</a>.</li><li>Advising is available online or in person.</li><li>Learn more on our <a href="/advising-support/career-services">Career Services page.</a></li></ul><hr><h2>Mental Health Counseling</h2><p>Information School students have access to mental health support from a mental health professional. The counselor can help you find referrals to short- and long-term therapy, provide support through a variety of mental health issues, both virtually and in-person, and give information about other resources. <a href="https://ischool.uw.edu/advising-support/mental-health-counseling">Learn about mental health counseling options</a>.</p><h2>Additional Advising Support</h2><p>Check the <a href="https://ischool.uw.edu/advising-support/additional-advising-support">Additional Advising Support page </a>for details on:</p><ul><li>Professional development panels, employer sessions and advising events</li><li>Engaging with faculty</li><li>Peer support</li><li>Professional organizations and mentors</li><li>Academic policies and procedures</li><li>iSchool graduate-level grading guidelines</li></ul><p class="MsoNormal">*Advisors and other Student Services staff at the iSchool are "Campus Security Authorities" under the<a href="https://police.uw.edu/clery-information/"> Clery Act </a>and must report some criminal actions and hate-related crimes to UWPD&nbsp;when disclosed. Issues involving citizenship or immigration status are&nbsp;<strong>not</strong>&nbsp;reported.</p><h2>Email &amp; Listservs</h2><p><a href="/advising-support/email-listservs">Learn about how Student Services communicates with you</a>.</p>
  </div>

</article>




              

